    "accordion_inline_zKGeqc": {
      "type": "accordion_inline",
      "blocks": {
        "accordion_item_JRziEF": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can you fix my hockey gear and skates?",
            "content": "We have an expert on-site who can help you with fixing your equipment. We won’t be happy until you are with your gear, and we will make sure to work on your gear efficiently and with great detail.<br><br>\nRepairs Available at the Hockey Shop include:<br><br>\n\nPlayer Glove Sewing<br>\nLeg Pad Binding Repairs<br>\nRe-lacing Catcher Pockets<br>\nMounting\/Riveting Holders<br><br>\n\nIn case you do not find the repair service you need on our list, please feel free to reach out to us via phone or email. Our team will do their best to identify and solve your problem, and work on your gear accordingly.<br><br>\n\nIf, for any reason, your hockey equipment cannot be repaired, our team of experts can assist you in finding new gear. We have extensive knowledge in this field and can help you choose the perfect gear that matches your preferences and style."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_Cc6HrL": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Can you sharpen my hockey skates?",
            "content": "We also cater to Skate Sharpening needs.<br><br>\n\n\n\nPlease see the following sharpening options we offer:<br><br>\n\nBlademaster – Traditional Hollow, or ROH<br>\nBlademaster – Flat Bottom Hollow (Blade Form Dressing, or BFD)<br>\nBlackstone – Flat Bottom V (FBV)<br>\nPro-Sharp – Z-Channel<br>\nSparx – Traditional Hollow, or ROH<br><br>\nFor a more in-depth explanation about different sharpening styles, or if you need help figuring out which one is best for you, feel free to come in or contact The Hockey Shop for further assistance."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_pqgjDK": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "What is Skate Profiling?",
            "content": "It's possible to skate and play well with the manufacturer's profile. However, the issue is that those profiles are not customized to fit you. Profiling considers various aspects of your play and you, including your height and weight, sharpening style (hollow), player position and skill level, ice hardness, previous profile, skate brand\/family\/holder size, foot position, leg shape, arm length, goals for improving your skating, and current balance and base position, maneuverability, speed, and style (goalies). <br><br>\n\nThe Hockey shop offer different options of Skate Profiling:<br><br>\n\nSingle Radius<br>\nDouble Radius<br>\nTriple Radius<br>\nQuad Radius<br>\nEllipse <br><br>\nWe understand that profiling can be complex, so we have expert staff on-site to help answer any questions and assess your playing style."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_MCJEKP": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "I want to know more about Custom Skate Fitting",
            "content": "The Hockey Shop is one of a few stores in North America that offers a Custom Skates Fitting from leading brands:<br><br>\n\nMyBauer Fit Station and Program<br>\nCCM Total Custom and Total Custom Plus <br>\nTRUE Fit Centre<br><br>\n If you are looking to get custom skates that are designed to fit you perfectly, we can assist you. However, understanding all the technical details and getting the measurements right can be quite challenging. To make things easier, you can contact The Hockey Shop by sending an email to sales@thehockeyshop.com or by calling <a href=\"tel:604-589-8299\">604-589-8299 <\/a>to book a skate fitting appointment."
          }
        },
        "accordion_item_tD9Mpc": {
          "type": "accordion_item",
          "settings": {
            "title": "Do you customize jerseys?",
            "content": "The Hockey Shop provides custom NHL jerseys for those who want to add a little more flair to their cheering.<br> Our professional Team Sales department is dedicated to creating custom gear for teams, and we assure you that the same level of quality and attention to detail will be applied to your custom NHL jersey.<br><br> Our team takes care of customization options such as names and numbers. If you want a custom jersey made, contact our Team Sales via call <a href=\"tel:1-800-567-7790\">1-800-567-7790<\/a> or email <a href=\"mailto:teamsales@thehockeyshop.com\">teamsales@thehockeyshop.com<\/a> to start your custom order."
          }
        }
      },
